# Trivy ignore file — CVEs triaged as accepted risk or false positives.
# One CVE ID per line. See: https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/
#
# When adding an entry, include: CVE ID, affected component, link, and rationale.

# CVE-2025-7458 — libsqlite3-0 in Debian bookworm
# https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-7458
# SQLite integer overflow. Debian bookworm has no fix version available.
# Accepted: sqlite in this image is the system package used by Python; the
# vulnerability requires a crafted database file and is not exploitable via
# the Python API calls made by this project.
CVE-2025-7458

# CVE-2023-45853 — zlib1g in Debian bookworm
# https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-45853
# Integer overflow and heap-based buffer overflow in zipOpenNewFileInZip4_6.
# Debian marks this as will_not_fix for bookworm.
# Accepted: the overflow requires a specially crafted ZIP file; this image
# does not process untrusted ZIP archives.
CVE-2023-45853

# CVE-2025-68121 — ollama Go stdlib crypto/tls
# https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-68121
# Incorrect certificate validation during TLS session resumption in Go <1.24.13.
# Ollama v0.21.0 is built with Go 1.24.1.
# Accepted: ollama in this image runs locally and does not make outbound TLS
# connections to untrusted servers. Pending ollama rebuild with Go 1.24.13+.
CVE-2025-68121